args: Hmm? Is someone crying?\nWho could it be?
I think it came from over here...
Her door's slightly ajar. That must be\nwhy her voice is carrying.
I was right—she IS crying. Should I say\nsomething to her? Or would that just\nmake everything worse?
Agh, I can't take it! It's too much!\nHow could this happen?!
I'm sorry for intruding, but I can't help\nthinking you're upset about a matter of\ntruly grave import—huh?
You're...reading. Wait, were you crying\nbecause of a BOOK?
AH! N-no! I certainly wasn't feeling\nemotional because of this book!
Oh? Then what is troubling you?
You can talk to me about it, if you like.
Everyone's been so kind to me here;\nmaybe this is a chance to return the favor.
Fine. I lied. I'm crying about the book.
Well, as you now know half of my dark\nsecret, I might as well tell the rest...
Er, are you not familiar with the genre?

I fear not. We didn't have much contact
with the outside world in the village,
and the variety of our book selection
was...limited.
Are these ＂romance novels＂ some kind of\nhistorical epoch?
Oh dear. Perhaps it would be easier for\nyou to read this one and see for yourself.
It might be good for you to expand your\nliterary horizons, after all.
Fair enough. Let me see here...
Ah, it seems this is the story of a brave\nknight and the prince she serves.
Ah! I mean, um...ha? Ha ha ha ha!\nWh-what a totally random coincidence!\nWhatever are the odds of that?!
Er, but please do go on. It really is a\nrather good story.

Let's see... Ah, so the knight and prince
grow closer to each other, then fall in love
despite the difference in social standing.
How very interesting.
Melsa?! Your face is bright red!
I, um...yes. I get rather...embarassed when\nit comes to romance. My apologies.
In that case, perhaps I should be the one\nwho is apologizing.
I'd thought you might become a fellow fan\nof the genre if I let you read one.
You really must love these books,\nElisanne.
It makes me a touch jealous.
If you like romance novels, you probably\ndon't get embarrassed thinking about the\nsubject, correct?
The subject of romance in general?\nNo, I suppose not.
Although I'm definitely no expert.\nQuite the opposite, in fact.
Oh, romance is far from a talent of mine.\nI can't even tell people how I feel...
Does that mean you have feelings for\nsomeone at this very moment?
Wait, er, n-no! It was...a metaphor!\nYes, that's it. A metaphor.
Now please just forget I said it.
And if you CAN'T forget it, at least don't\nask me anything else; I'm so embarrassed,\nI feel as if my heart is going to explode.
In truth, my heart is racing as well, so I\ncouldn't possibly press for more details.
I would very much like to know what it's\nlike to be in love like that.
I think you just might have more bravery\nthan I do when it comes to romance.
Oh, I don't think I'm so courageous as\nall that.
Don't worry yourself. You're eventually\ngoing to find someone to love, and they\nwill love you back without reservation.
I pray you find your love as well!
